      • getBoundingBox

        public java.awt.Rectangle getBoundingBox()
        Returns bounding box of the given element. The upper left corner of this bounding box rectangle is the 'anchor' for the element, and all drawing is relative to it. A copy of the current bounding box is returned for protection, so it isn't inadvertently modified by code external to this class.
        Returns:
        bounding box for element.
